> It's easy to get into the al fresco spirit when you've got burgers featuring an
> Italian topping trio of mozzarella, tomato, and basil. The classic red, white,
> and green combo makes this more than just another burger recipe, adding a blast
> of fresh flavors and cheesy goodness. And although we recommend cooking the
> beef patties on the grill for maximum summertime vibes, you can also make them
> on the stovetop, if that's more your style.

== Prep ==

Wash and dry all produce. Trim stem ends from @zucchini{2%unit}, then halve
lengthwise. Slice halves lengthwise into ¼-inch-thick planks. Place in a
#medium bowl{} and toss with a large drizzle of @olive oil{1%tablespoon}. Season
with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Set aside. Split @ciabatta bread{4%unit} in half,
then brush cut sides with a drizzle of olive oil.

Preheat a #grill{} for direct heat and brush grates with a drizzle of
@vegetable oil{1%tablespoon}.

> TIP: If cooking indoors, heat a #grill pan{} or #large pan{} over medium-high
> heat.

Place ciabattas on grill or in pan cut-side down. Toast until light golden,
~{2-3%minutes}. Set aside on a #plate{}.

== Patties ==

In a #large bowl{}, mix @ground beef{20%ounce}, half the @parmesan cheese{1/4%cup},
@italian seasoning{1%teaspoon}, salt, pepper, and a pinch of
@chili flakes{1%teaspoon}.

> Use more chili flakes for extra heat.

Shape into four 1-inch-thick patties. Lightly brush grill grates with another
drizzle of vegetable oil (or heat a drizzle of oil in pan). Add patties and cook
until marks appear on bottom, ~{4-5%minutes} (don't flip just yet).

While patties cook, slice @fresh mozzarella{4%ounce} into four equally thick
slices. Slice @tomato{1%unit} crosswise into four rounds. Pick
@basil{1/2%ounce} leaves from stems; discard stems.

After patties have cooked ~{4-5%minutes}, flip and cook on other side for
~{1%minute}, then top each with a slice of mozzarella. Cover grill or pan and
cook until mozzarella melts, about ~{3%minutes}.

== Spicy Balsamic Ketchup ==

Mix @ketchup{4%tablespoon}, @balsamic glaze{5%teaspoon}, and a pinch of
@chili flakes{1%pinch} in a #small bowl{}.

> Use more chili flakes to taste if desired.

Spread mixture onto cut-side of ciabattas. Fill ciabattas with a slice of tomato
and a patty each. Top patties with basil leaves. Set aside.

== Grilled Vegetables ==

Lightly brush grill grates with another drizzle of vegetable oil (or heat a
drizzle of olive oil in your pan).

Add zucchini to grill or pan and cook until marks appear, about ~{2%minutes}.
Flip and sprinkle with remaining parmesan. Cover grill or pan and cook until
tender and grill marks appear on other side, about ~{2%minutes}.

Divide zucchini and burgers between #plates{} and serve.